data.title: CITY MOVIE GUIDE
data.text:
CAPITOL.?** "The Naked Jungle," technicolor romantic

adventure, starring Charlton Heston, Eleanor Parker.

Plus "The Wife of Monte Cristo," adventure, starring

John Loder, Lenore Aubert, Eva Gabor.

CENTURY.?** "A Man Called Peter." CinemaScope

drama, in Delux color, starring Richard Todd, Jean

Peters. Plus featurettes. ,

ESQUIRE.?+ "The Americano," technicolor adventure.

starring Glenn Ford. Frank Lovejoy. Ursula Thiess, Cesar

Romero. Plus * "Hell Raiders of the Deep," underwater

adventure, starring Eleanor Rossi Drago, Pierre Cressoy.

LIBERTY.?** "Interrupted Melody," CinemaScope

musical drama in color, starring Eleanor Parker, Glenn

Ford. Plus featurettes.

LYCEUM.?-** Phffft," comedy, starring Judy Holliday.

Jack Carson, Jack Lemmon, Kim Novak. (See review

this page.) Plus "The Nebraskan." technicolor Western,

starring Phil Carey, Roberta Haynes, Wallace Ford.

MAYFAIR.?* "Not As A Stranger," drama, starring Olivia

de Havilland. Robert Mitchum, Frank Sinatra, Gloria

Grahame. Phis featurettes.

PALACE.?* "Crossed Swords," Pathecolor period adven-

hire, starring Errol Flynn, Gina Lollobrigida. Plus

"The Marshal's Daughter," Western, starring Laurie

Anders. Hoot Gibson.

PARIS.?*** "Gate of Hell," Japanese Eastmancolor

drama, starring Kazuo Hasegawa, Machiko Kyo. Plus

featurettes.

PLAZA.?** "Violent Saturday," CinemaScope Delux

color thriller, starring Victor Mature, Richard Egan.

Virginia Leigh. Plus * "Atomic Kid," comedy, starring

Mickey Rooney. Robert Strauss, Elaine Davis.

REGENT. *** "Daddy Long Legs," CinemaScope Delux

color musical, starring Fred Astaire, Leslie Caron. Plus

featurettes.

ST. JAMES.--* "Green Fire," Eastmancolor CinemaScope

outdoor adventure, starring Stewart Granger, Grace Kelly.

Plus featurettes.

SAVOY.--** "Umberto D," Italian drama, with English

subtitles, starring Carlo Barristi, Maria Pia Casilia. Lina

Gennari. Plus ** "Stars of the Russian Ballet," techni-

color ballet feature.

STATE.--* "The Sea Shall Not Have Them," sea drama,

starring Michael Redgrave, Dirk Bogarde, Anthony Steel,

Nigel Patrick. Plus featurettes.

Films not yet reviewed

EMBASSY. --?"Geordie." technicolor comedy, starring Bill

Travers. Alastair Sim, Norah Gorsen. Plus featurettes.

LYRIC.-- "Revenge of the Creature," science-fiction thriller,

starring John Agar, Lori Nelson, John Bromfield. Plus

"Tomahawk," technicolor Western, starring Van Heflin,

Yvonne de Carlo, Jack Oakie. (Re-release.)

PALLADIUM.--"Malaga," technicolor adventure, starring

Maureen O'Hara, Macdonald Carey. Plus "Devil Girl

From Mars." Science-fiction, starring Hugh McDermott,

Hazel Court.

PRINCE EDWARD.-- "Rear Window," technicolor thriller.

starring James Stewart, Grace Kelly, Wendell Corey,

Plus featurettes.

VICTORY.-- "The Shrike," drama, starring Jose Ferrer,

June Allyson. Plus "Man From Bitter Ridge," Eastman-

color Western, starring Lex Barker, Mara Corday.
